import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    women_data = data[data['sex'] == 'women']
    women_data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(women_data['year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    women_data = women_data.groupby(['job', 'year'])['perc'].sum().unstack('job')
    
    for job in women_data.columns:
        plt.plot(women_data.index, women_data[job], label=job)
    
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Percentage of Women')
    plt.title('What is the overall trend in the percentage of women in different job occupations over the years?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.legend(loc='best', fontsize='small')
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    top_occupations = data.groupby('job')['count'].sum().sort_values(ascending=False).head(10)
    top_occupations.plot(kind='bar')
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title("What are the top 10 job occupations with the highest number of individuals working in them?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    top_occupations = data.groupby(['job']).agg({'perc': 'sum'}).nlargest(5, 'perc').reset_index()
    top_occupations_data = data[data['job'].isin(top_occupations['job'])]
    pivot_data = top_occupations_data.pivot_table(index='job', columns='sex', values='perc', aggfunc='sum')
    pivot_data.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True, ax=plt.gca())
    
    plt.title("What is the gender distribution in the top 5 job occupations with the highest percentage of individuals working in them?", wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    top_5_jobs = data.groupby('job')['count'].sum().nlargest(5).index
    top_5_data = data[data['job'].isin(top_5_jobs)]
    
    for job in top_5_jobs:
        job_data = top_5_data[top_5_data['job'] == job]
        plt.plot(job_data['year'], job_data['count'], label=job)
    
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Individuals')
    plt.title('What is the trend in the number of individuals working in the top 5 job occupations over the years?')
    plt.legend()
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
